article.description: Chris Rodgers and Arizona tuned up for the postseason with another rout of their archrival.
article.headline: Stoudamire, Adams score 21 apiece
article.linkText: Arizona closes regular season with win over ASU
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Ike Diogu scored 25 points, grabbed eight rebounds and blocked six shots to lead Arizona State past EA Sports 73-58 in an exhibition game Tuesday night. Diogu had 15 points, six rebounds, three assists and three blocked shots in the first half as the Sun Devils led 44-24 at halftime. Arizona State took advantage of EA Sports' 33 percent shooting (7 of 21) and 12 first-half turnovers. EA Sports went on a 16-0 run in the second half to close to 67-54 with 3:36 remaining but never got closer. Chris Jeffries had 13 points and Mark Green added 11 for EA Sports. Arizona State opens the regular season here Sunday against Jackson State.
